The paper presents an algorithm that uses statistical learning models to induce non-monotonic logic programs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also makes use of Explainable AI tools, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses the High-Utility Itemset Mining (HUIM) problem, which is a data mining technique, suggesting that it could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) or Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories.
